Postgres won&#39;t know that `g` in the SQL command is supposed to be the value of a C variable. It doesn&#39;t know anything about C variables. You will need to construct the SQL command in an array of `char` using `sprintf` and pass that to `PGexec`.

For example:

        char pgcmd[100];

        sprintf(pgcmd, &quot;insert into modbus_value(id,temp) values(1,%g)&quot;, g);
        res = PQexec(conn, pgcmd);

